My name is Will Hutnick and I am an artist living and working in Brooklyn.  I graduated from Providence College in 2007 and got my M.F.A. at Pratt Institute in 2011.  I play the cello in the Brooklyn Symphony Orchestra, and I'm usually covered in paint.This past year, my work and I have travelled all over the NYC metro area, including:
a summer residency on Governors Island, where I created an installation, "Atlas", composed of strips of tape directly on the wall;

to Bushwick and Crown Heights, where I curated the exhibitions "Future Folk: Part 1 & 2" at Brooklyn Fire Proof and LaunchPad with Polly Shindler;

to Chelsea, where I transformed a pop-gallery via Uprise Art into my studio for two weeks;

back to Bushwick, where I opened my studio to the public for Bushwick Open Studios;

and even to Bedminster, NJ, where I exhibited my work in a solo show, "He Chutes He Scores", at The Center for Contemporary Art.

It's been a busy year already, and I'm not done yet.I am excited to head to Johnson, Vermont, this October to immerse myself in my work and practice and make a huge mess at Vermont Studio Center.  I will have four weeks to just paint and draw and create.  I will have the opportunity to experiment and expand my vocabulary; to meet and inspire new artists that share a similar drive and passion; to reflect and find new meanings and new directions in my work; to grow and take risks.With your generous support, I will be able to create work in an environment where my only job is to create work.  I am defraying some of the costs of the program with an artist's grant and work exchange, but it is expensive for an artist who is usually slinging cocktails a few nights a week to get by.  In exchange for your help, I will give you stickers and original art.  Win Win WIN.Your support will enable me to fully realize all that this residency has to offer.  As my Mom would say, this is the "GIFT OF TIME"; it's a fantastic opportunity to challenge myself and guide my work to the next level, whatever that might be.Thank you for your help - I look forward to sharing my work and progress with you!
